    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> alexcrichton submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12315#pullrequestreview-4510462598\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 603930387,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1781647591
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12315#discussion_r3424314747\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Could this be moved to <code>crates/core/src/array.rs</code> so this could get miri-testing there, and additionally enable adding <code>#[test]</code> for this? Additionally, this doesn't currently handle panics of <code>cb</code> (leaks intermediate results) and a few more casts than I think are necessary.</p>\n<p>I sketched out what I'm thinking <a href=\"https://gist.github.com/alexcrichton/6a50596ac126a56609c9a60a5bf34fd1\">here</a> and feel free to copy that into this PR</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 603930389,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1781647591
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12315#discussion_r3424173045\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>This is fine yeah, it's proportional to what the guest has already done. Before this loop is done, though, can this call <code>consume_fuel_array</code> in the same manner as lists?</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 603930390,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1781647591
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12315#discussion_r3424224115\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I've got some miscellaneous concerns about this function, so I'm going to list them here:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>This is more-or-less duplicated with <code>new_fixed_length_list_type</code> in <code>types_builder.rs</code>. Could that call this function (or a similar signature?)</li>\n<li>I'm worried about the unchecked multiplication here because the host could declare <code>[SomeBigStruct; HUGE_NUMBER]</code> which exceeds 4GiB of data, and I'd want that to be a panic/error/something as opposed to the silent wrap here.</li>\n<li>I think the <code>saturating_mul</code> here should be <code>checked_mul</code>, and I also don't think the conversion here to <code>u8</code> is right. If <code>c</code> is 1 and <code>count</code> is 256 then <code>flat_count</code> should be <code>None</code>, not <code>Some(255)</code>.</li>\n<li>I'm a little worried that in Rust below we've got <code>N: usize</code> where the parameter <code>count: u32</code> has a different type here. Could there be a separate entrypoint which takes <code>count: usize</code> and performs a fallible/panicking conversion asserting that the <code>count</code> is less than <code>u32::MAX</code>?</li>\n</ul>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 603930391,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1781647591
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12315#discussion_r3424145277\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Nah this is fine, this is where there's basically no other option.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 603930393,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1781647591
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12315#discussion_r3424181962\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>This is fine yeah, but similar to above can this use <code>consume_fuel_array</code> beforehand?</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 603930394,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1781647591
    },
